cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.CVPR

This paper deals with computer vision tasks such as obstacle detection, segmentation, and classification using self-supervised learning approaches. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel framework for learning offline clusters and using them as pseudo labels for real-time image classification, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The application of this framework is in autonomous driving systems, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also uses deep learning techniques for image classification, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper presents its results at the Conference on Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (CVPR), which is a subcategory of cs.CV.
